author: Russell Brand
description:
What counts as a curse word these days? In this fun (and very sweary) segment, we dive into the global hierarchy of swearing — from “wanker” to the C-word — and what they reveal about culture, censorship, and Britishness abroad. Plus, a few thoughts on Tommy Robinson, the watershed, and the charming chaos of English insults.

This clip is taken from our Watch Along of Tommy Robinson's documentary 'Silenced', check out the full episode - https://www.youtube.com/live/wdXUIF7J0mY
